A `!` followed by an identifier does, yes. But a `!` also lets you define diverging functions:<p><pre><code>    fn diverging() -> ! {
        unreachable!()
    }
</code></pre>
The two `!` in that code are completely orthogonal things. See the manual on diverging functions: <a href="http://doc.rust-lang.org/rust.html#diverging-functions" rel="nofollow">http://doc.rust-lang.org/rust.html#diverging-functions</a>
